sql:
SELECT errors.severity_id, errors.error_message, severities.severity_name
FROM errors
JOIN severities ON errors.severity_id = severities.severity_id;

SELECT DISTINCT dt.diag_type_name, dt.description
FROM diagnostic_types dt
INNER JOIN errors e ON dt.diag_type_id = e.diag_type_id;

SELECT name 
FROM errors 
WHERE diag_type_id NOT IN (SELECT diag_type_id FROM diagnostic_types);

external_knowledge:
- "oasis of high-severity diagnostics" refers to the diagnostic types with high severity errors;
- "desert nomads known as developers" refers to the users with the role 'developer';
- "born in the recent sands of time (last month)" refers to errors created in the last month;
- "rainfall (frequency)" metaphorically represents the count of errors;
- "date of each storm (error occurrence)" refers to the date when the error was created.

sql:
SELECT diag_type_name 
FROM diagnostic_types
WHERE LOWER(diag_type_name) = 'unknown';

external_knowledge:
- "issues" refers to "error";
- "diagnostic procedures" refers to "diagnostic type";
- "staff" refers to "users";
- The phrase "encountered more than one problem" refers to the count of errors being greater than one.

sql:
SELECT file_name
FROM error_attachments
WHERE file_type = 'text/plain' AND file_size > 500;

SELECT error_message, error_stack_trace, debuggable
FROM errors
ORDER BY severity_id ASC;

SELECT updated_at 
FROM errors 
WHERE error_id = 1;
